short.am,ar,bg,bn,ca,cs,da,de,el,en,en_AU,en_G: This extension allows switching to open tabs using Cmd+double-digit numbers

long.am,ar,bg,bn,ca,cs,da,de,el,en,en_AU,en_G:
Have you ever tried tab switching using cmd+[1-9]? Ever wished cmd+9 would take you to the 9th tab instead of the last one? Well then, welcome to the Two-digit Tab Switcher!

Using this extension, you can not only switch to the 9th tab using cmd+9 but also easily switch to tab 18 by pressing cmd+1,8. cmd+0 takes you to the last tab.
